reviewText: With Sheryl Crow strumming her guitar, along with the band, this concert has the added bonus of having an orchestra accompanying her on some songs.  She especially seemed to love the fiddle on one song.  Get it whether you are a die-hard Crow fan or just want to see a nice, pleasant concert.

reviewText: This DVD is done very well!The sound quality is near perfect(especially in stereo mode), & so is the camera work!The mix of songs are good, and Sheryl's voice is spectacular through out!I had read in one of the other reviews that Sheryl looks tired, so I will comment on that remark.Yes, she seems to do a little less dancing around etc... than previous concerts I have seen, but she also sings a lot of slower songs(hence the wildflower tracklist), on this dvd so she is in a little slower mode some of the songs.I give this dvd full stars, and am looking forward to her latest concert dvd release, SOUNDSTAGE, that just came out a few weeks ago.Also, soundstage is starting to relase several past shows on dvd, and new shows on dvd.Just look up soundstage in the search bar on Amazon.comThanks for reading my review...
